# Provenance manifest for the committed structural snapshots
#
# This file documents WHERE each `specs/fixtures/*.h5ls` snapshot came from.
# It is NOT a CI gate. The default (CI-reproducible) validator mode checksums the
# small committed `*.h5ls` snapshots themselves; the big-table `sha256` recorded
# here is verified only by the opt-in provenance/refresh mode
# (`WL_TABLES_ROOT=... bash specs/tools/validate_specs.sh`), which re-derives each
# snapshot from the live multi-GB `.h5` table and SKIPS loudly when the tables are absent.
#
# Format: one record per pinned production table, blank-line separated.
#   key: value
#
# Fields:
#   table            basename of the production .h5 file (relative to $WL_TABLES_ROOT)
#   source_set       provenance / version note for the table set
#   weaklib_commit   weaklib source revision whose writers produced this on-disk layout
#   table_sha256     sha256 of the live multi-GB .h5 (refresh-mode check only)
#   snapshot         the committed specs/fixtures/*.h5ls produced by `h5ls -r <table>`
#   snapshot_sha256  sha256 of the committed snapshot (default-mode CI check)
#
# Snapshots were generated once with:
#   h5ls -r <table> > specs/fixtures/<basename>.h5ls
# from the canonical clean production set at
#   /Users/liwei/Datas/wl_tables/use_for_production/
# (h5ls 1.14.x, HDF5 from /opt/homebrew). Re-derive with refresh mode to confirm no drift.

source_set: weaklib production SFHo set, use_for_production (clean canonical copy)

